  "summary": "Moderate: usbguard security update",
  "details": "The USBGuard software framework provides system protection against intrusive USB devices by implementing basic whitelisting and blacklisting capabilities based on device attributes. To enforce a user-defined policy, USBGuard uses the Linux kernel USB device authorization feature.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* usbguard: Fix unauthorized access via D-Bus (CVE-2019-25058)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
